KING et al., Respondents, v. METROPOLITAN EL. RY. CO., Appellant. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. May 18, 1894.) Action by David I. King and others against the Metropolitan Elevated Railway Company.

Argued before VAN BRUNT, P. J., and FOLLETT and PARKER, JJ.

I. A. Murray, for appellant A. O. Townsend, for respondents.

No opinion. Order affirmed, with $10 costs and disbursements.
